      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of Oct 17 article: New York University gets some $8 million in research money from Defense Department that could be jeopardized if it bars military recruiters, not over $200 million</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article yesterday about a protest against a military recruiter at New York University Law School over the military's ban on openly gay service members misstated the amount of research money the university receives from the Defense Department, which has threatened to withhold funds from universities that bar recruiters. It is about $8 million, not more than $200 million.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>An article yesterday about a protest against a military recruiter at New York University Law School over the military's ban on openly gay service members misstated the amount of research money the university receives from the Defense Department, which has threatened to withhold funds from universities that bar recruiters. It is about $8 million, not more than $200 million.</p>
